710802f-a.text:
Twelfth Avenue, at W.59th Street. Shown are the vast New York Central Railroad yards sprawled out along the Hudson River. The views are in a southerly direction from the mid-W.60's toward 59th Street, where the large power plant of the Interborough subway system can be seen.
P.L.Sperr  1924
Views 1,2

710803f-a.text:
Twelfth Avenue, north of W.59th Street, showing the extensive New York Central Railroad yards, looking north. On the right are warehouses and
apartment houses in the W.60's.
P.L.Sperr  April 14, 1924
Views 1,2
